American Art Since 1900
Praeger | 1975 | ISBN: 0275439003 | English | 322 pages | PDF | 47.1 MB


Since it was first published in 1967, this brilliant critical history of modern art in America has become a classic in the field. Now, Barbara Rose, an increasingly popular critic and writer, has brought her account of American painting and sculpture up to the mid-1970s, offering a coherent, insightful interpretation of the often confusing, though always fascinating, developments during the past decade
